docs.snippet: In a story Aug. 13 about Gov. Rick Perry's border security strategy, The Associated Press erroneously reported that the Texas Department of Public Safety said that 203,000 immigrants illegally in the U.S. have been charged since 2008 with more tha...
docs.lead_paragraph: In a story Aug. 13 about Gov. Rick Perry's border security strategy, The Associated Press erroneously reported that the Texas Department of Public Safety said that 203,000 immigrants illegally in the U.S. have been charged since 2008 with more than 3,000 homicides and 8,000-plus sexual assaults. The agency said the immigrants have been charged in that many crimes over their criminal careers, not just since 2008.
